article.description: — Tyren Moore's 27 points helped Georgia Southern defeat Southern Miss 88-67 in a Sun Belt Conference opener on Saturday night.
article.headline: Moore's 27 lead Georgia Southern over Southern Miss 88-67
article.linkText: Moore's 27 lead Georgia Southern over Southern Miss 88-67
article.story: STATESBORO, Ga. -- — Tyren Moore's 27 points helped Georgia Southern defeat Southern Miss 88-67 in a Sun Belt Conference opener on Saturday night. Moore had six rebounds and five assists for the Eagles (1-12). Eren Banks scored 12 points, going 5 of 11 (2 for 6 from 3-point range). Mannie Harris had 12 points and shot 4 for 7 from beyond the arc. The win snapped a 12-game slide for the Eagles. Andre Curbelo led the Golden Eagles (6-7) in scoring, finishing with 18 points, seven rebounds and four steals. Austin Crowley added 15 points for Southern Miss. Donovan Ivory also had 10 points and four steals. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
